dy and the social and historical context of its performance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/75208540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292762695423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292762695/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK